    "The framework above can be extended to predict other atmospheric variables available in TEMPO data such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **CO (Carbon Monoxide)**: Similar approach but with different feature engineering\n",
    "- **HCHO (Formaldehyde)**: Requires attention to different seasonal patterns\n",
    "- **Aerosols**: May need additional meteorological features\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Features of the Predictive System:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Spatial-Temporal Modeling**: Incorporates both geographic location and time-based features\n",
    "2. **Multiple Model Comparison**: Trains and compares different algorithms\n",
    "3. **Feature Engineering**: Creates lag features, rolling statistics, and spatial interactions\n",
    "4. **Forecast Visualization**: Maps and time series plots for understanding predictions\n",
    "5. **Uncertainty Quantification**: Can be extended to include prediction intervals\n",
    "\n",
    "### Next Steps for Production Use:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data Collection**: Fetch multiple TEMPO granules across extended time periods\n",
    "2. **Model Validation**: Cross-validation with held-out temporal periods\n",
    "3. **Ensemble Methods**: Combine multiple models for better accuracy\n",
    "4. **Real-time Updates**: Incorporate latest observations to update forecasts\n",
    "5. **Meteorological Integration**: Add weather data for improved predictions"
